{
  "texts": [
    "Mangrove forests, another critical component of the coastal and marine sector, offer a range of ecosystem services, including coastal protection, carbon sequestration, and habitat provision (Maina et al., 2021).",
    "Coastal wetlands, including saltmarshes and peat swamp forests, also face significant risks due to climate change (Wen and Hughes, 2022).",
    "Sea-level rise poses a direct threat to these wetlands, leading to habitat loss and altered ecosystem functions.",
    "Changes in disturbance dynamics, such as increased flooding and erosion, further exacerbate these vulnerabilities.",
    "Understanding the complex interplay of factors affecting coastal wetland resilience is crucial for assessing our resilience in the face of climate change."
  ]
}